The Blue Mountains is densely populated by oil bearing Eucalyptus trees. The atmosphere is filled with finely dispersed droplets of oil#Comma which#Comma in combination with dust particles and water vapour#Comma scatter short-wave length rays of light which are predominantly blue in colour.

In the past couple of years#Comma the winds of transformation have been blowing in along the Coast#Comma bringing with them a five-star resort#Comma cool gallery spaces#Comma newsworthy authentic Mexican#Comma vintage upcycled threads#Comma floral artistry#Comma and fine dining to rival the best of big cities.

The state’s 300km-long Oyster Coast – stretching south of Sydney – is scattered with oyster farms. Many specialise in succulent rock oysters#Comma which are known for their intense#Comma tangy flavour. Try them fresh in the shell with a squeeze of lemon.

The state’s and Australia's oldest wine region produces high-quality shiraz#Comma cabernet sauvignon#Comma semillon and merlot#Comma with dozens of top-notch wineries and cellar doors open for visits and tastings.
